1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:02,420
Now we will start building our model.

2

00:00:02,420  -->  00:00:08,600
We will go through it step by step and learn about how every part of it is structured,

3

00:00:08,600  -->  00:00:12,670
and we will gradually build it in PyTorch.

4

00:00:12,670  -->  00:00:19,130
The first step of our model is to process the input that was sent to it.

5

00:00:19,130  -->  00:00:25,840
We would need to tokenize the input and convert each token into a token ID.

6

00:00:25,840  -->  00:00:31,500
Then we'll convert each token into a corresponding word embedding.

7

00:00:31,500  -->  00:00:36,860
After this step, instead of having a vector with three token IDs,

8

00:00:36,860  -->  00:00:40,460
we'll have a matrix with three vectors,

9

00:00:40,460  -->  00:00:45,805
and each vector will be an embedding for a corresponding input token.

10

00:00:45,805  -->  00:00:49,120
A few things to note about this output.

11

00:00:49,120  -->  00:00:51,320
First, the word embeddings,

12

00:00:51,320  -->  00:00:56,040
the model selects depends solely on the token IDs.

13

00:00:56,040  -->  00:00:57,940
For the same token ID,

14

00:00:57,940  -->  00:01:01,960
we will always get the same word embedding vector.

15

00:01:01,960  -->  00:01:07,625
Second, these word embeddings will be trained together with our model.

16

00:01:07,625  -->  00:01:09,530
We don't define them upfront.

17

00:01:09,530  -->  00:01:12,580
They are defined during our models training.

18

00:01:12,580  -->  00:01:14,500
To create an instance of this class,

19

00:01:14,500  -->  00:01:19,240
we'll need to specify the size of our vocabulary, which in this case,

20

00:01:19,240  -->  00:01:21,620
we arbitrary set to 10,000,

21

00:01:21,620  -->  00:01:27,800
and we need to specify the size of each embedding vector which we'll set to 75.

22

00:01:27,800  -->  00:01:31,360
Then we'll create an instance of the nn embedding and

23

00:01:31,360  -->  00:01:36,080
provide both the vocabulary size and the size of the embedding vectors.

24

00:01:36,080  -->  00:01:41,560
To use it, we need to get a list of token IDs we want to convert to embedding vectors.

25

00:01:41,560  -->  00:01:45,640
Here we define arbitrary IDs, but in our code,

26

00:01:45,640  -->  00:01:50,300
we will use a tokenizer to convert tokens into token IDs.

27

00:01:50,300  -->  00:01:54,980
Then we pass token IDs to the instance of nn embedding.

28

00:01:54,980  -->  00:01:58,440
Embedding will produce a tensor with four vectors,

29

00:01:58,440  -->  00:02:04,370
each of size 75 which is the size of embedding vector we've selected.

30

00:02:04,370  -->  00:02:06,390
As you can see from this shape,

31

00:02:06,390  -->  00:02:12,010
the nn embedding returns an embedding vector per each input token ID.

32

00:02:12,010  -->  00:02:15,450
Before we can send these embedding vectors to our model,

33

00:02:15,450  -->  00:02:18,090
we need to do one more thing.

34

00:02:18,090  -->  00:02:21,330
We need to take another matrix called

35

00:02:21,330  -->  00:02:26,250
positional encoding and add it to the word embeddings.

36

00:02:27,730  -->  00:02:32,390
Positional encoding is another matrix that allows us

37

00:02:32,390  -->  00:02:37,150
to inject positional information about input tokens.

38

00:02:37,150  -->  00:02:44,110
This information will help the model to understand the relative order of input tokens.

39

00:02:44,110  -->  00:02:49,550
The positional encoding matrix is fixed and does not depend on the input.

40

00:02:49,550  -->  00:02:56,855
We simply add the same values for every single set of word embeddings our model receives.

41

00:02:56,855  -->  00:02:59,070
Where do we get these values?

42

00:02:59,070  -->  00:03:02,290
In some models, including the ones that we will build,

43

00:03:02,290  -->  00:03:06,460
these are trained together with other model parameters.

44

00:03:06,460  -->  00:03:08,790
But in some other LLMs,

45

00:03:08,790  -->  00:03:14,890
these are defined using a complex formula and don't change during training.
